The paper deals with network augmentation and optimization, which is a topic that falls under computational geometry (cs.CG) and data structures (cs.DS). The use of shortcuts to minimize the continuous diameter involves graph theory and discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The algorithms and optimization techniques used in the paper also fall under numerical analysis (cs.NA) and optimization (cs.SI).
